            "heading": "<p>Arch Pain</p>",
            "heading_size": "title-md",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "highlighted_text": "text",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Arch pain, also known as arch strain, involves inflammation and/or a burning sensation at the arch of the foot. Various factors can cause arch pain, including structural imbalances or foot injuries. The most common cause of arch pain is Plantar Fasciitis, a condition affecting the plantar fascia, a fibrous tissue band running from the heel to the forefoot.<br/><br/>If untreated and strain on the longitudinal arch continues, a heel spur, a bony protrusion, may develop. Prompt treatment is essential to prevent<br/> the condition from worsening.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
